1. Q1. A user tries to replicate an existing EC2 instance by selecting the "Launch More Like This" option. However, the AMI linked to the original instance has been deleted. What is the outcome in this situation?
      Options:

      A. The instance will still launch without needing the original AMI.
      B. The instance will start, but a new AMI won't be generated.
      C. AWS will automatically create a new AMI and proceed with the launch.
      D. An error will occur, indicating that the required AMI has been deregistered. [CORRECT]

2. A solutions architect is designing a high performance computing (HPC) workload on Amazon EC2. The EC2 instances need to communicate to each other frequently and require network performance with low latency and high throughput.
    Which EC2 configuration meets these requirements?
    
    A. Launch the EC2 instances in a cluster placement group in one Availability Zone. [Correct]
    B. Launch the EC2 instances in a spread placement group in one Availability Zone.
    C. Launch the EC2 instances in an Auto Scaling group in two Regions and peer the VPCs.
    D. Launch the EC2 instances in an Auto Scaling group spanning multiple Availability Zones.
    
      
